obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31793)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The words "except Part B States" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31793&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Manoeuvres, Field Firing and Artillery`
  line `Practice Act, 1938.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31794)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Power of State Government to authorise manoeuvres.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31794&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the local Official Gazette, authorise the execution of military manoeuvres over any area`
  line `specified in the notification during a specified period not exceeding three months:`
  line
  line `Provided that the same area or any part thereof shall not ordinarily be so specified more than once in`
  line `any period of three years.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall publish notice of its intention to issue a notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) as early as possible in advance of the issue of the notification, and no such notification`
  line `shall be issued until the expiry of three months from the date of the first publication of such notice in the`
  line `local Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) The notice required by sub-section (2) shall be given by publication in the local Official Gazette`
  line `and shall also be given throughout the area which it is proposed to specify in the notification by`
  line `publication in the manner prescribed by rules made under section 13, and shall be repeated by like`
  line `publication one month and one week as nearly as may be before the commencement of the manoeuvres.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31795)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Powers exercisable for purposes of maneuvers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31795&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a notification under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 has been issued, such persons as are included in the military forces engaged in the`
  line `manoeuvres may, within the specified limits and during the specified periods,--`
  line
  line `(a) pass over, or encamp, construct military works of a temporary character, or execute military`
  line `manoeuvres on, the area specified in the notification, and`
  line
  line `(b) supply themselves with water from any source of water in such area:`
  line .
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall authorise the taking of water from any source of supply,`
  line `whether belonging to a private owner or a public authority, of an amount in excess of the reasonable`
  line `requirements of the military forces or of such amount as to curtail the supply ordinarily required by those`
  line `entitled to the use of such water supply.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not authorise entry on or interference with any well or tank`
  line `held sacred by any religious community or any place of worship or ground attached thereto except for the`
  line `legitimate purpose of offering prayers or any place or building reserved or used for the disposal of the`
  line `dead, or any dwelling house or premises attached thereto or any educational institution, factory, workshop`
  line `or store or any premises used for the carrying on of any trade, business or manufacture or any garden or`
  line `pleasure ground, or any ancient monument as defined in section 2 of the Ancient Monuments`
  line `Preservation Act, l904 (7 of 1904).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31796)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Duty of Officer Commanding to repair damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31796&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Officer in Command of the military`
  line `forces engaged in the manoeuvres shall cause all lands used under the powers conferred by this Chapter to`
  line `be restored, as soon and as far as practicable, to their previous condition.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31797)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Right to compensation for damage caused by manoeuvres.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31797&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where a notification issued under`
  line `section 2 authorises the execution of military manoeuvres compensation shall be payable from the`
  line `Defence Estimates for any damage to person or property or interference with rights or privileges arising`
  line `from such manoeuvres including expenses reasonably incurred in protecting person, property, rights and`
  line privileges.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31798)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Method of assessing compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31798&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector of the district in which any area utilised`
  line `for the purpose of manoeuvres is situated shall depute one or more Revenue Officers to accompany the`
  line `forces engaged in the manoeuvres for the purpose of determining the amount of any compensation`
  line `payable under section 5.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revenue Officer shall consider all claims for compensation under section 5 and determine, on`
  line `local investigation and where possible after hearing the claimant, the amount of compensation, if any,`
  line `which shall be awarded in each case; and shall disburse on the spot to the claimant the compensation so`
  line `determined as payable.`
  line
  line `(3) Any claimant, dissatisfied with a refusal of the Revenue Officer to award him compensation or`
  line `with the amount of compensation awarded to him by the Revenue Officer, may, at any time within fifteen`
  line `days from the communication to him of the decision of the Revenue Officer, give notice to the Revenue`
  line `Officer of his intention to appeal against the decision.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any such notice has been given, the Collector of the district shall constitute a commission`
  line `consisting of himself as chairman, a person nominated by the Officer Commanding the forces engaged in`
  line `the manoeuvres and two persons nominated by the District Board, and the commission shall decide all`
  line `appeals of which notice has been given.`
  line
  line `(5) The commission may exercise its powers notwithstanding the absence of any member of the`
  line `commission, and the chairman of the commission shall have a casting vote in the case of an equal division`
  line `of opinion.`
  line
  line `(6) The decision of the commission shall be final and no suit shall lie in any Civil Court in respect of`
  line `any matter decided by the commission.`
  line
  line `(7) No fee shall be charged in connection with any claim, notice, appeal, application or document`
  line `filed before the Revenue Officer, Collector or the commission under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31799)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31799&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If, within the area and during the period specified in a notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2, any person--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully obstructs or interferes with the execution of the manoeuvres, or`
  line
  line `(b) without due authority enters or remains in any camp, or`
  line
  line `(c) without due authority interferes with any flag or mark or any apparatus used for the purposes`
  line `of the manoeuvres,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ten rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31800)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31800&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) "field firing" includes air armament practice;`
  line
  line `(b) "notified area" means an area defined in a notification issued under sub-section @I@(1) of`
  line `section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31801)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of State Government to authorise field firing and artillery practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31801&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the local Official Gazette, define any area as an area within which for`
  line `a specified term of years the carrying out periodically of field firing and artillery practice may be`
  line authorised.
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification in the local Official Gazette, authorise the carrying`
  line `out of field firing and artillery practice throughout a notified area or any specified part thereof during any`
  line `period or periods specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Before any notification under sub-section (2) is issued, the State Government shall publish notice`
  line `of its intention to issue such notification as early as possible in advance of the issue of the notification,`
  line `and no such notification shall be issued until the expiry of two months from the date of the first`
  line `publication of the notice in the local Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(4) The notice required by sub-section (3) shall be given by publication in the local Official Gazette`
  line `and shall also be given throughout the notified area by publication in some newspaper circulating in and`
  line `in the language commonly understood in that area and by beat of drum and by affixation in all prominent`
  line `places of copies of the said notice in the language of the locality and in such other manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under section 13 and shall be repeated by like publication one week as nearly as`
  line `may be before the commencement of the period or of each period specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fact of the said beat of drum and affixation shall be verified in writing by one`
  line `headman and two other literate inhabitants of the locality and provided further that such notice by the beat`
  line `of drum shall be given seven and two days as nearly as may be before the commencement of such field`
  line `firing and artillery practice.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (31802)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Powers exercisable for purposes of field firing and artillery practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31802&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a`
  line `notification under sub-section(2) of section 9 has been issued, such persons as are included in the forces`
  line `engaged in field firing or artillery practice may, within the notified area or specified part thereof during`
  line `the specified period or periods,--`
  line
  line `(a) carry out field firing and artillery practice with lethal missiles, and`
  line
  line `(b) exercise, subject to the provisions of sections 3 and 4, any of the rights conferred by section 3`
  line `on forces engaged in military manoeuvres:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 3 shall not debar entry into, or`
  line `interference with, any place specified in that sub-section, if it is situated in an area declared to be a`
  line `danger zone under sub-section (2) of this section, to the extent that may be necessary to ensure the`
  line `exclusion from it of persons and domestic animals:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a dwelling house occupied by women adequate warning shall`
  line `be given through a local inhabitant and entry shall be effected after such warning in the presence of`
  line `two respectable inhabitants of the locality.`
  line
  line `(2) The Officer Commanding the forces engaged in any such practice may, within the notified area or`
  line `specified part thereof, declare any area to be a danger zone, and thereupon the Collector shall, on`
  line `application made to him by the Officer Commanding the forces engaged in the practice, prohibit the entry`
  line `into and secure the removal from such danger zone of all persons and domestic animals during the times`
  line `when the discharge of lethal missiles is taking place or there is danger to life or health.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (31803)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31803&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 5 and 6 shall apply in the case of field firing and`
  line `artillery practice as they apply in the case of military manoeuvres:`
  line
  line `Provided that the compensation payable under this section shall include compensation for exclusion`
  line `or removal from any place declared to be a danger zone of persons or domestic animals, such`
  line `compensation to be disbursed at not less than the minimum rates prescribed by rules made under`
  line `section 13 before the exclusion or removal is enforced, and shall also include compensation for any loss`
  line `of employment or deterioration of crops resulting from any such exclusion or removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (31804)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31804&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If, during any period specified in a notification issued under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 9, any person within a notified area--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully obstructs or interferes with the carrying out of field firing or artillery practice, or`
  line
  line `(b) without due authority enters or remains in any camp, or`
  line
  line `(c) without due authority enters or remains in any area declared to be a danger zone at a time`
  line `when entry thereto is prohibited, or`
  line
  line `(d) without due authority interferes with any flag or mark or target or any apparatus used for the`
  line `purposes of the practice,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to ten rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (31805)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667&sectionId=31805&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00026_193805_1535002455667
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] The State Government may, by notification in the local Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules`
  line
  line `(a) prescribing the manner in which the notices required by sub-section (2) of section 2 and`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 9 shall be published in the areas concerned;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the use under this Act of land for manoeuvres or field firing and artillery practice in`
  line `such manner as to secure the public against danger and to enable the manoeuvre, or practice, to be`
  line `carried out without interference and with the minimum inconvenience to the inhabitants of the areas`
  line affected;
  line
  line `(c) regulating the procedure of the Revenue Officers and commissions referred to in section 6 in`
  line `such manner as to secure due publicity regarding the method of making claims for compensation and`
  line `preferring appeals from original awards of compensation, the expeditious settlement of claims and of`
  line `appeals and the payment of compensation so far as possible direct to the claimants; and`
  line
  line `(d) defining the principles to be followed by the Revenue Officers and commissions referred to in`
  line `section 6 in assessing the amount of compensation to be awarded.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 13 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
